# Table Pattern

## Shell

Use the project’s table shell (`DataTableShell`, `EnterpriseDataTable`, shared `data-table`) — do not invent a one-off table chrome.

## Must-haves

- Search (debounced) with clear control
- Column headers with sort when data supports it
- Pagination or virtualization for large sets
- Sticky header when scrolling
- Row actions menu (edit/view/delete) — consistent placement
- Loading skeleton + empty + error states

## Filters

Prefer compact icon/filter triggers over always-open filter bars that steal vertical space.

## RTL

Arabic headers and actions; keep numeric/code columns `tabular-nums` / LTR when needed.

## Money & dates

Format via shared `formatCurrency` / date helpers — never ad-hoc string concat.
